    <h2> FACT 1: THE AMAZING OCTOPUS </h2>
    <p> octupus have three hearts,nine brains and blue blood.Two hearts pump blood to the grills,while the third pumps it to the rest of body. </p>

    <h3>How smart are octopuses?</h3>
    <p>Octopuses can open jars, solve puzzles, and even recognise human faces. Scientists consider them one of the most
        intelligent invertebrates on Earth.</p>
    
    <h2>⚡ Fact 2: Lightning Strikes</h2>
    <p>Lightning strikes the Earth about 100 times every single second. That is roughly 8 million lightning strikes per day!
    </p>
    
    <h3>How hot is lightning?</h3>
    <p>A single bolt of lightning is around 30,000 Kelvin – five times hotter than the surface of the Sun.</p>
    
    <h4>Can lightning strike twice?</h4>
    <p>Yes! Lightning absolutely can and does strike the same place more than once, especially tall structures like towers
        and trees.</p>
    
    <h2>🌊 Fact 3: The Deep Ocean</h2>
    <p>More than 80% of the world's oceans remain unexplored. Scientists believe there are many species living in the deep
        sea that we have never discovered.</p>
    
    <h3>How deep does the ocean go?</h3>
    <p>The deepest point on Earth is the Mariana Trench, which reaches a depth of about 11 kilometres – deep enough to fit
        Mount Everest inside with room to spare!</p>
        <h5> Fun comparison </h5>
        <p> If you placed MOUNT EVEREST at the bottom of mariana Trench, it's peak would still be  more than 2 kilometres underwater. </p>
